1
00:00:23,423 --> 00:00:30,964
<i>(Usagi) Eah! Oh, no! My mom ‐</i>
<i>who, by the way, makes the best</i>
<i>lemon pie in Japan ‐ no, in the</i>
<i>world ‐ no, in the universe ‐</i>

2
00:00:31,031 --> 00:00:34,801
<i>my mom is having an affair?!</i>
<i>That's totally bananas!</i>

3
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,437
<i>How dare you seduce a happily</i>
<i>married homemaker!</i>

4
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,774
<i>In the name of my dad, I'll</i>
<i>punish you!</i>

5
00:01:03,704 --> 00:01:05,506
<i>Sailor Moon...</i>

6
00:01:05,906 --> 00:01:06,707
<i>SuperS!</i>

7
00:01:07,407 --> 00:01:12,378
Sailor Moon SuperS

8
00:02:18,885 --> 00:02:21,755
<i>(Chibi‐Usa) Pegasus?...Pegasus,</i>
<i>is that you?</i>

9
00:02:22,956 --> 00:02:29,630
<i>(Pegasus) Time is running</i>
<i>out...I must hurry before the</i>
<i>dark skies cover the Crystal</i>
<i>Forest in blackness.</i>

10
00:02:29,963 --> 00:02:33,800
(Chibi‐Usa) <i>Wait! Pegasus! There</i>
<i>are so many more things I wanna</i>
<i>ask you!</i>

11
00:02:33,934 --> 00:02:36,436
<i>(Pegasus) When you are in</i>
<i>trouble, call my name.</i>

12
00:02:36,603 --> 00:02:38,805
<i>(Chibi‐Usa) Pegasus!...Pegasus!</i>

13
00:02:45,478 --> 00:02:45,812
[gasp]

14
00:02:47,413 --> 00:02:48,515
Pegasus...

15
00:02:52,485 --> 00:02:55,589
<i>"Protect Mom's Dream:</i>
<i>Double Moon's New Attack"</i>

16
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,868
(Usagi) <i>I'm home!</i>

17
00:03:03,670 --> 00:03:11,344
Ooh, what's that [sniffing] My
favorite smell! Ya‐hoo! Mom's
homemade, one‐of‐a‐kind...!

18
00:03:11,444 --> 00:03:13,313
[chomping]

19
00:03:13,514 --> 00:03:16,016
...lemon meringue pie!...
[scream]

20
00:03:17,884 --> 00:03:20,320
Wait! What happened to it?
Where's mine? Huh? Huh!

21
00:03:20,386 --> 00:03:23,023
[chewing]...Ahh...

22
00:03:23,156 --> 00:03:23,957
Ahh...!

23
00:03:24,024 --> 00:03:24,891
Not for you...[chomp]

24
00:03:25,025 --> 00:03:26,560
What, why not?

25
00:03:27,994 --> 00:03:30,396
Because Mommy Ikuko baked this
pie 'specially for us, as a
reward.

26
00:03:30,731 --> 00:03:31,732
Reward for what?

27
00:03:35,536 --> 00:03:38,204
[gasp] Perfect scores?! Wha‐
How'd you two‐

28
00:03:39,405 --> 00:03:43,810
Well, yeah, but the questions on
your tests are so easy, it's not
that hard to get a hundred
percent.

29
00:03:43,877 --> 00:03:47,013
<i>(Ikuko) That's pretty bold talk,</i>
<i>coming from someone with a score</i>
<i>like this.</i>

30
00:03:50,917 --> 00:03:54,655
Yaah! And I even hid that in a
box, under the rug, under my
bed‐‐!

31
00:03:54,855 --> 00:03:56,022
Wow, that's pathetic.

32
00:03:56,089 --> 00:03:57,658
Well, you got your name right.

33
00:03:59,593 --> 00:04:03,036
Math wasn't exactly my best
subject in school either, but
this, Usagi, this is just
terrible.

34
00:04:03,570 --> 00:04:06,607
(Chibi‐Usa) <i>You're</i>
<i>single‐handedly bringing the</i>
<i>whole family's average down!</i>

35
00:04:07,574 --> 00:04:11,678
But, still, it's pretty mean to
punish me by starving me to
death!

36
00:04:11,912 --> 00:04:12,746
Uh?

37
00:04:15,081 --> 00:04:18,418
You made one of your famous
lemon meringue pies and I don't
get a single piece? That's just
cruel! Cruel! Cruel! Cruel!

38
00:04:18,552 --> 00:04:22,255
What do you mean? I cut enough
slices for everybody. What
happened to them?

39
00:04:22,589 --> 00:04:24,758
What?...Chibi‐Usa!

40
00:04:26,292 --> 00:04:30,230
Her pie is irresistible!
I couldn't help myself...
[blowing raspberry]

41
00:04:30,296 --> 00:04:32,633
Chibi‐Usa, you pie stealing
cheater! I want my piece of pie!

42
00:04:32,766 --> 00:04:35,902
You get back here and give me
back the piece of pie you
just ate!

43
00:04:35,969 --> 00:04:39,639
All right, all right, now. Just
calm down. You're the big
sister, remember.

44
00:04:39,906 --> 00:04:40,907
[growl] So what?!

45
00:04:41,908 --> 00:04:43,443
Mom, you're spoiling Chibi‐Usa
way too much!

46
00:04:45,712 --> 00:04:47,814
You probably don't know this,
but spoiling and pampering a
child too much can put a real
strain on your marriage!

47
00:04:47,948 --> 00:04:49,415
I read about it in a magazine!

48
00:04:49,482 --> 00:04:51,384
Don't lie to me, Usagi! You
never read!

49
00:04:53,319 --> 00:04:56,790
I knew it. It's obvious
Chibi‐Usa's more important to
you than I am. Why don't you
just admit it?

50
00:04:57,390 --> 00:05:00,967
It's just a piece of pie! Will
you please stop making such a
big deal about it!

51
00:05:01,101 --> 00:05:02,936
[whimpering]

52
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,506
I hate you, mom!

53
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:05,906
[gasp]

54
00:05:14,848 --> 00:05:16,750
Sometimes I don't know what to
do with her...

55
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:17,851
You said it.

56
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,655
<i>(Minako) You're running away</i>
<i>from home because of that?</i>

57
00:05:21,855 --> 00:05:26,660
It figures it had to be a fight
over food. That's so you, Usagi.
You're always losing it‐

58
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:31,665
It's not about food! Before the
pie, there was the time she ate
my wasabi rice crackers, the
ones that I'd been saving,...

59
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:35,869
...and my fudge pebble ice
cream,...and my seaweed‐flavored
potato chips,...and‐

60
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,470
So it is about food.

61
00:05:37,538 --> 00:05:39,005
If I was your mom, I'd disown
you.

62
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,442
Whatever the reason, it's not
worth holding a grudge over.

63
00:05:45,712 --> 00:05:49,650
You guys just don't get it. Mom
always takes her side, in
everything!

64
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:55,021
Chibi‐Usa is just clearly more
important to her than I
am!...[crying]

65
00:05:55,121 --> 00:05:56,523
Oksy, it's okay...

66
00:05:57,991 --> 00:06:00,026
No mother ever thinks that one
child is more important than the
other.

67
00:06:01,668 --> 00:06:03,870
Yeah, and remember, right now,
Chibi‐Usa's living far away from
her real parents.

68
00:06:05,639 --> 00:06:11,377
She's at an age when she needs a
lot of attention. Maybe what you
need to do is try to be a little
more patient with her.

69
00:06:11,912 --> 00:06:13,547
[gasping]

70
00:06:19,052 --> 00:06:22,488
<i>(Fish's Eye) That makes twice in</i>
<i>a row, now, you've struck out</i>
<i>with women, Tiger's Eye...</i>

71
00:06:22,556 --> 00:06:24,825
<i>You think you might be losing</i>
<i>your touch?</i>

72
00:06:24,891 --> 00:06:26,727
Me? Don't be absurd!

73
00:06:28,394 --> 00:06:30,931
The girls were putty in my hands
until those darn Sailor
Guardians came butting in.

74
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:37,237
If you ask me, you've been
going about it all
wrong...Deception is the surest
way into a woman's heart.

75
00:06:37,571 --> 00:06:43,243
(Tiger's Eye) <i>That one, Hawk's</i>
<i>Eye?...Well, you did always have</i>
<i>a thing for older women.</i>

76
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:45,712
Hey. You're invading my personal
space.

77
00:06:45,779 --> 00:06:46,513
Oh!

78
00:06:47,213 --> 00:06:47,714
The thing about older women...

79
00:06:49,683 --> 00:06:52,586
<i>(Hawk's Eye) One, they're</i>
<i>grateful. And two, you can</i>
<i>play on their maternal</i>
<i>instincts.</i>

80
00:06:54,855 --> 00:06:56,790
[slurp]

81
00:06:58,458 --> 00:07:01,034
They don't call me Hawk's Eye
the Madamkiller for
nothing...Just watch and learn.

82
00:07:08,742 --> 00:07:13,479
Usagi's not back, yet...I wonder
if she's still angry.

83
00:07:14,548 --> 00:07:15,415
Mommy Ikuko‐ [gasp]

84
00:07:15,481 --> 00:07:18,418
Ooh, wow, what are
you looking at, in here?

85
00:07:19,319 --> 00:07:21,421
Cool! They're old family
photos!

86
00:07:21,555 --> 00:07:24,791
That's right. I thought it was
time I tried to organize them a
little.

87
00:07:25,659 --> 00:07:27,628
This one's funny! Who's this?

88
00:07:27,728 --> 00:07:31,598
Oh, that?...That's Usagi when
she was a little baby, don't you
recognize her?

89
00:07:31,732 --> 00:07:34,668
(Chibi‐Usa) <i>[giggle] Not</i>
<i>through all that dirt!</i>
<i>[giggling]</i>

90
00:07:34,801 --> 00:07:35,602
And this?

91
00:07:37,137 --> 00:07:39,405
(Ikuko) <i>That's her in her</i>
<i>Kindergarten play. (tch) She was</i>
<i>the bunny.</i>

92
00:07:41,474 --> 00:07:46,479
Oh, here's one. Look at
this...Her first day of
elementary school. Oh...She
looks just like you, Chibi‐Usa.

93
00:07:46,613 --> 00:07:47,981
<i>(Chibi‐Usa) She does!</i>

94
00:07:50,016 --> 00:07:55,522
<i>But,...all these pictures are of</i>
<i>Usagi...There's not a single one</i>
<i>of me.</i>

95
00:07:56,923 --> 00:07:59,660
(Ikuko) <i>Looking at these, I see</i>
<i>a dream coming true.</i>

96
00:07:59,793 --> 00:08:01,635
[gasp] )...You do?

97
00:08:03,436 --> 00:08:06,873
Yeah. These photos are a record
of the dream I've always had of
watching you, Usagi, Shingo,

98
00:08:07,007 --> 00:08:09,610
everyone in the family growing
up healthy and happy.

99
00:08:10,043 --> 00:08:11,545
That's a beautiful dream.

100
00:08:13,113 --> 00:08:15,516
And, out of all of them, I'd
have to say this one is my
current favorite.

101
00:08:16,983 --> 00:08:17,651
[gasp]

102
00:08:20,053 --> 00:08:23,289
(Chibi‐Usa) <i>You're right...It's</i>
<i>a good one</i>

103
00:08:24,024 --> 00:08:30,363
And one day, I hope I can put
photos in our family album of
you and Usagi going up the aisle
in your wedding dresses.

104
00:08:30,864 --> 00:08:32,833
That's my biggest dream, now.

105
00:08:33,299 --> 00:08:34,701
[sigh]

106
00:08:35,902 --> 00:08:40,240
I'm sorry I ate Usagi's pie. Now
she'll never come home.

107
00:08:40,373 --> 00:08:44,578
Huh? Oh, don't worry about that.
She'll come one home when she
gets hungry.

108
00:08:45,378 --> 00:08:51,818
And when she does, you really
should tell her you're sorry.
You know how touchy she can get
over food, especially desert.

109
00:08:52,318 --> 00:08:52,886
Hm!

110
00:09:01,401 --> 00:09:02,402
[exhale]

111
00:09:04,004 --> 00:09:05,906
(Ami) <i>Right now, Chibi‐Usa's</i>
<i>living far away from her real</i>
<i>parents.</i>

112
00:09:07,407 --> 00:09:09,409
<i>Maybe what you need to</i>
<i>do is try to be a little</i>
<i>more patient with her.</i>

113
00:09:12,345 --> 00:09:17,584
Ami's right. She's doing her
best, considering she's in a
different time period. Maybe
I'll head back.

114
00:09:18,351 --> 00:09:20,754
We could make a lotta lemonade
with all these!

115
00:09:20,887 --> 00:09:25,258
Yes, we could, but what I'm
going to do instead is bake
some more lemon meringue pies.

116
00:09:25,391 --> 00:09:27,961
I'm betting Usagi will be drawn
back home by the smell.

117
00:09:28,595 --> 00:09:32,966
(Hawk's Eye) <i>She's got a kid</i>
<i>with her. Well that's okay.</i>
<i>Might make it even better.</i>

118
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:35,769
[yell]

119
00:09:35,869 --> 00:09:38,872
Aah! Our lemons!...[gasping]

120
00:09:38,939 --> 00:09:40,907
Here, let me help...!

121
00:09:41,642 --> 00:09:42,909
Oh, my. Thank you.

122
00:09:44,778 --> 00:09:45,278
Uh?

123
00:09:45,378 --> 00:09:47,280
No! It can't be! [gasp]

124
00:09:47,413 --> 00:09:49,550
W‐what is it? What's wrong?

125
00:09:49,616 --> 00:09:53,319
[weeping]...Mommy!

126
00:09:53,587 --> 00:09:53,920
Huh?

127
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,488
Whaa‐‐? Uhh‐‐!

128
00:09:55,989 --> 00:09:56,923
Mommy!

129
00:09:57,791 --> 00:09:59,760
Uh‐ I'm sorry?

130
00:10:00,426 --> 00:10:03,203
Oh...Please. Forgive me.

131
00:10:03,570 --> 00:10:08,341
You just look so much like my
long‐lost mother that, for a
moment, I thought‐‐ [weeping]

132
00:10:08,408 --> 00:10:10,410
Your mother...you lost her?

133
00:10:11,011 --> 00:10:16,449
I have one picture of her, taken
a long time ago...Where is it‐‐?
Oh, here it is...

134
00:10:16,717 --> 00:10:18,919
It's the only image of my mother
that I have.

135
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:20,954
[gasps]

136
00:10:22,022 --> 00:10:22,856
[deep inhales]

137
00:10:24,558 --> 00:10:26,727
I thought I'd finally found a
ray of hope...!

138
00:10:27,027 --> 00:10:30,964
...After all the years and the
thousands of miles I've
traveled, searching for
Mommy...!

139
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:32,398
(Chibi‐Usa) <i>Poor guy.</i>

140
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:36,570
Oh, dear. If you don't mind my
asking, what was your mother's
name?

141
00:10:38,539 --> 00:10:38,972
Ikuko.

142
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:39,973
[gasps]

143
00:10:40,941 --> 00:10:43,409
Ikuko Nicolaevich Blavatsky.

144
00:10:43,710 --> 00:10:45,378
Definitely a different person.

145
00:10:46,446 --> 00:10:48,782
Yes, I'm sorry, but you have the
wrong woman.

146
00:10:50,884 --> 00:10:54,788
I see that now. How could I have
thought that someone as young
and beautiful as you could've
been her.

147
00:10:54,888 --> 00:10:55,421
[gasp]

148
00:10:55,956 --> 00:10:57,991
Excuse me, I think I'm‐

149
00:10:58,559 --> 00:11:00,801
[gasp]...What's wrong? Are you
all right?

150
00:11:01,835 --> 00:11:04,270
Haven't eaten anything for
days...

151
00:11:04,638 --> 00:11:05,806
Ohh, you poor thing!

152
00:11:07,473 --> 00:11:11,444
How I wish I could taste my
mother's pickled rutabage one
last time...[croak]

153
00:11:11,778 --> 00:11:14,615
Oh, my goodness! I don't think I
have any of that.

154
00:11:14,681 --> 00:11:16,349
Pickled rutabaga...

155
00:11:16,482 --> 00:11:17,784
I'll go back to the store!

156
00:11:17,851 --> 00:11:19,319
Yes, go and buy some!

157
00:11:19,452 --> 00:11:19,820
Hm!

158
00:11:20,521 --> 00:11:22,288
[chuckling]

159
00:11:48,048 --> 00:11:51,151
Chibi‐Usa! What are you doing in
this part of town all by
yourself?

160
00:11:51,284 --> 00:11:54,855
Never mind me, where have you
been? We've got a situation!

161
00:11:55,288 --> 00:11:56,056
Huh?

162
00:11:56,389 --> 00:11:57,791
You feeling better now?

163
00:11:57,891 --> 00:11:58,391
Yes.

164
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:05,038
You're as kind‐hearted as you
are beautiful. I have a thing
for kind‐hearted, beautiful
women.

165
00:12:05,138 --> 00:12:05,806
Huh?

166
00:12:09,075 --> 00:12:11,044
You said she was helping a
starving man!

167
00:12:11,144 --> 00:12:11,878
What's going on?

168
00:12:13,246 --> 00:12:15,381
Our meeting like this, it has to
be much more than just a
coincidence.

169
00:12:15,481 --> 00:12:17,884
I really‐ I really don't think
it is!

170
00:12:18,184 --> 00:12:19,485
Mom's having an affair...!

171
00:12:21,087 --> 00:12:24,490
A kind and beautiful person like
you...I bet you have the most
beautiful dreams.

172
00:12:26,226 --> 00:12:27,761
[gasps]

173
00:12:27,861 --> 00:12:29,162
[shuddering]

174
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,236
[bleating]

175
00:12:36,436 --> 00:12:37,037
One...!

176
00:12:37,203 --> 00:12:38,238
[scream]

177
00:12:39,039 --> 00:12:39,506
Two...!

178
00:12:40,541 --> 00:12:41,241
[yowl]

179
00:12:41,441 --> 00:12:42,242
And three!

180
00:12:42,342 --> 00:12:46,947
[scream]

181
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,448
We have to transform, now!

182
00:12:48,582 --> 00:12:49,449
I can see that!

183
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:55,255
(Chibi‐Usa) <i>Moon Prism Power</i>
<i>Make Up!</i>

184
00:13:02,202 --> 00:13:06,973
(Usagi) <i>Moon Cosmic Power Make</i>
<i>Up!</i>

185
00:13:38,338 --> 00:13:41,107
Now let me have a look at that
beautiful dream of yours.

186
00:13:41,174 --> 00:13:43,009
[gasp]

187
00:13:45,512 --> 00:13:46,112
[chuckle]

188
00:13:46,647 --> 00:13:46,980
(Usagi) <i>Hold it!</i>

189
00:13:47,413 --> 00:13:47,981
Who's there?!

190
00:13:49,249 --> 00:13:51,952
<i>(Usagi) You creep, how dare you</i>
<i>try to seduce a busy mother</i>

191
00:13:52,018 --> 00:13:55,121
<i>who devotes her life to taking</i>
<i>care of the house and raising</i>
<i>her children!</i>

192
00:13:56,022 --> 00:13:59,192
I'm Sailor Moon...Guardian of
love and justice!

193
00:13:59,325 --> 00:14:01,034
And I'm Sailor Chibi Moon!

194
00:14:02,335 --> 00:14:04,938
And now, in the name of the
Moon,...we'll punish you!

195
00:14:05,038 --> 00:14:06,206
...we'll punish you!

196
00:14:08,174 --> 00:14:13,213
I take it you're those pesky
Sailor Guardians. Come forth, my
Lemures, Ms. Do Kanko, the Human
Cannon!

197
00:14:23,557 --> 00:14:24,290
[gasps]

198
00:14:25,391 --> 00:14:28,194
Step one: swab the barrel! Step
two: load the barrel!

199
00:14:28,294 --> 00:14:30,396
What are you...doing?...Hello?

200
00:14:31,231 --> 00:14:33,066
Step three: light the fuse!

201
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:40,073
Step four: the
countdown!...Three,...two,...one
,...and fire!

202
00:14:40,206 --> 00:14:40,473
[gasp]

203
00:14:41,041 --> 00:14:41,474
[high‐pitch twittering]

204
00:14:41,842 --> 00:14:43,076
[yelling]

205
00:14:43,176 --> 00:14:44,477
(Minako) <i>Venus Love Me Chain!</i>

206
00:14:44,578 --> 00:14:46,513
[low‐pitch twittering]

207
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:47,180
Oof!

208
00:14:47,247 --> 00:14:47,748
[BOOM]

209
00:14:48,248 --> 00:14:49,850
Oof! [thud]

210
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:50,984
Are the two of you all right?

211
00:14:51,985 --> 00:14:54,387
Yyyeahhhh...

212
